Cell.Text: Sorry, I thought Skald the Elder sent you. We've got an order to fill, and he's not known for patience. | Look, if you're heading towards Dawnstar anytime soon, can you give the Jarl this note? Let him know he'll get his lumber.

Falkreath is known for its graveyard, traveler. We've buried more dead than you can imagine. | I just finished giving my old war companion, Berit, a proper burial by fire. Old hard head hated the idea of being lost cold in the ground. | Could you deliver the ashes to Urunil, the priest of Arkay? He'll know the right blessings to make for Berit's soul.
What kind of writing do you do?

I write drama, friend. The legends and history of Skyrim made to excite and inspire. | Poor Giruad Gemane at the Bard's College has been waiting for my latest work, "Olaf and the Dragon," for weeks now. Roads are a mess.
How long have you been training dogs?

My family has been doing it for years. You need one out in the Reach. Don't want to be alone when some Forsworn comes swinging. | I personally trained a whole litter for the Jarl. That reminds me, I was going to deliver some dog food to the Keep. Spiced beef. Their favorite.
You've been working in the mines long?

This mine is only a few years old, but I've been digging up ore for over a century. | We're getting to the point where the tunnels are getting deep into the rock. People complain of bad coughs and foul air. | I've seen this before. We need some medicines to combat the ore dust. I was about to send a message to Windhelm for aid.

My brother is... sensitive. He has trouble focusing his attention on things. | We were taking him to the Temple of Kynareth in Whiterun, just so the healers could make sure he was in good health, and they say he's fine. | Are you heading to Whiterun? Could you take this letter to the priestess, Danica Purespring? It's a note about Joric's health.
[S] You're sure? When you see Giruad, ask for a tip. I'm sure he'll be in a good mood after reading this.
[S] Well, look at you, thanks. Take it to Voada, she handles all the dogs for the Jarl.
I could deliver your message for you.
[S] Thank you. Take it to Quintus, in the White Phial.

Node.Caption: Favor001QuestAccept: I could deliver that for you.

Cell.Text: [S] What's this? Oh, that's right, the timbers from Anga's Mill. | I swear, that Aeri and her men would make a fine Stormcloak recruit. Pity we can't spare the lumber to conscript them. | Here. Take this. For your time and all that.
[S] Oh, thank you. The dogs were getting restless. | Here, this is for you.
[S] Ah, Berit's ashes. He was a good man. Not many warriors grow to a fine, old age. | Thank you for bringing this to me. I'll make sure he gets his rites. Here, for your trouble.
[S] Ah yes, Adonato's new work. Shorter than I expected, but words must be judged on merit, not length. | I'll look over this later. Why don't you take this, for your trouble?
[S] Oh dear. Darkwater Crossing needs medicines for its miners? | I'll see about getting this order filled right away. Here, a few Septims for you.
[S] Joric's sister? Poor child. Magic runs deep in that family's bloodline. It's not always a blessing. | Thank you for this. Something for your trouble.
